YouTube - Key Information

Platform Overview:
- Video sharing platform founded in 2005, acquired by Google in 2006
- One of the largest video platforms globally with billions of users
- Supports various content: music, tutorials, vlogs, documentaries, live streams

Key Features:
- Recommendation algorithm suggests personalized content
- Monetization through YouTube Partner Program (ads, sponsorships, memberships)
- YouTube Premium for ad-free viewing and offline downloads
- YouTube Shorts for short-form vertical video content
- Live streaming capabilities for creators

Content Categories:
- Entertainment, music, education, gaming, news, vlogs, tutorials
- Podcasts and audio content
- Educational channels and courses

Creator Tools:
- YouTube Studio for analytics and management
- Monetization requirements: 1,000 subscribers + 4,000 watch hours
- Copyright protection and content ID system
- Community tab for engaging with audience

User Features:
- Subscriptions to follow favorite creators
- Playlists and watch history
- Comments and likes for engagement
- Notifications for new uploads from subscribed channels

Trends:
- Growing focus on short-form content (Shorts)
- Increased live streaming adoption
- Educational and skill-based content growth
- Creator economy expansion